      "order": 1,
      "Description": "When technology teams move quickly to adopt AI tools, the excitement of innovation can easily outpace the policies and safeguards needed to keep things secure and compliant. This lesson explores the governance gaps that commonly emerge when AI is introduced without a clear framework, including issues around data privacy, accountability, and risk management. You will learn to recognise the warning signs that your team may be moving faster than your oversight structures can handle. By the end of this lesson, you will have a practical understanding of why governance matters and what steps you can begin taking to close those gaps. No prior experience with AI governance is required, just a willingness to think critically about how your team adopts new technology.",
